## Admin Dashboard Pattern

### Build Read-Only Metric Views

```typescript
// app/admin/growth/page.tsx

export default function GrowthMetricsPage() {
  const [metrics, setMetrics] = useState<Metrics | null>(null);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    const fetchMetrics = async () => {
      const [pmf, activation] = await Promise.all([
        fetchWithAuth('/api/pmf-survey'),      // GET endpoint
        fetchWithAuth('/api/activation'),       // GET endpoint
      ]);
      setMetrics({ pmf: await pmf.json(), activation: await activation.json() });
    };
    fetchMetrics();
  }, []);

  return (
    <>
      <DashboardNav />
      <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 py-16">
        <h1>Growth Metrics</h1>
        
        {/* Metric cards with target comparison */}
        <MetricCard
          label="PMF Score"
          value={`${pmf.score}%`}
          target={pmf.benchmark}
          passing={pmf.hasPmf}
        />
        
        {/* Detailed table for drill-down */}
        <UserActivationTable users={activation.users} />
      </div>
    </>
  );
}
```

**Why this pattern:**
- Admin pages use `DashboardNav` (authenticated)
- Parallel API calls for speed (`Promise.all`)
- Visual indicators for passing/failing (green/yellow/red)
- Drill-down tables for investigating outliers
- Read-only (no mutations in admin dashboards, keep them safe)

