## Copy-to-Clipboard Pattern (Referral Links)

```typescript
// app/components/WaitlistThankYou.tsx

const [copied, setCopied] = useState(false);

const handleCopy = async () => {
  if (!referralUrl) return;
  
  try {
    await navigator.clipboard.writeText(referralUrl);
    setCopied(true);
    setTimeout(() => setCopied(false), 2000);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Copy failed:', err);
    // Fallback: show alert with URL
    alert(`Copy this link: ${referralUrl}`);
  }
};

<button onClick={handleCopy}>
  {copied ? 'Copied!' : 'Copy'}
</button>
```

**Why this pattern:**
- Visual feedback (button text changes for 2 seconds)
- Fallback for older browsers (alert with URL)
- Error handling (clipboard API can fail on HTTP, works on HTTPS)

