## Computed Metrics (Calculate Server-Side)

### Days Active, Time-to-Activation, Cohort Membership

```typescript
// app/api/activation/route.ts (GET)

const users = await prisma.user.findMany({
  select: { createdAt: true, firstAutomatedTradeAt: true },
});

const usersWithMetrics = users.map(u => {
  const daysActive = Math.floor(
    (Date.now() - u.createdAt.getTime()) / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24)
  );
  
  const daysToActivation = u.firstAutomatedTradeAt
    ? Math.floor((u.firstAutomatedTradeAt.getTime() - u.createdAt.getTime()) / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
    : null;
  
  return {
    daysActive,
    daysToActivation,
    activated: daysToActivation !== null && daysToActivation <= 7,
  };
});
```

**Why server-side:**
- Consistent calculation (no client timezone issues)
- Easier to add to SQL queries later (computed columns)
- Single source of truth (if logic changes, update one place)

