## Migration Pattern

### Create Directory, Write SQL Manually

When adding growth schema changes:

```bash
# 1. Format and validate schema
npx prisma format

# 2. Create migration directory
mkdir -p prisma/migrations/$(date +%Y%m%d%H%M%S)_feature_name

# 3. Write migration.sql manually (safer than auto-generate for production)
```

```sql
-- prisma/migrations/.../migration.sql

-- Add nullable columns first (safe, no downtime)
ALTER TABLE "User" ADD COLUMN "firstAutomatedTradeAt" TIMESTAMP(3);

-- Add with defaults (safe)
ALTER TABLE "Waitlist" ADD COLUMN "referralCount" INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;

-- Create new tables
CREATE TABLE "PmfSurvey" (
    "id" TEXT NOT NULL,
    "userId" TEXT NOT NULL,
    ...
    CONSTRAINT "PmfSurvey_pkey" PRIMARY KEY ("id")
);

-- Add indexes last (can build concurrently in production)
CREATE INDEX "PmfSurvey_userId_idx" ON "PmfSurvey"("userId");
```

**Why manual SQL:**
- Auto-generated migrations can be destructive
- Manual review catches mistakes before prod
- Can add `CONCURRENTLY` for zero-downtime index builds
- Explicit control over migration order

