## Anti-Patterns

### ❌ Calculating Metrics Client-Side
```typescript
// Bad: timezone issues, inconsistent
const daysActive = Math.floor((new Date() - new Date(user.createdAt)) / 86400000);
```

Always compute dates/days server-side in the API, return the number.

### ❌ Storing Booleans Instead of Timestamps
```typescript
// Bad: loses "when" information
hasActivated: boolean

// Good: preserves timeline
firstAutomatedTradeAt: DateTime?
```

Use timestamps. You can always derive booleans (`!!timestamp`), but can't reverse it.

### ❌ Blocking Critical Paths on Metrics
```python
# Bad: trade fails if metrics API is down
record_activation(user)  # raises exception
place_order(symbol, qty) # never reached

# Good: metrics are non-critical
try:
    record_activation(user)
except:
    logger.warning("Metrics failed (non-critical)")
place_order(symbol, qty) # always runs
```

Metrics should never block core functionality.

